def test_delattr(self):
    params = params_dict.ParamsDict()
    params.override({
        'a': 'aa',
        'b': 2,
        'c': None,
        'd': {
            'd1': 1,
            'd2': 10
        }
    },
                    is_strict=False)
    del params.c
    self.assertEqual(params.a, 'aa')
    self.assertEqual(params.b, 2)
    with self.assertRaises(AttributeError):
      _ = params.c
    del params.d
    with self.assertRaises(AttributeError):
      _ = params.d.d1

smell.description: The attribute is deleted from an object through a dynamically determined name.
